<h1>Job Opportunities</h1>
<h3>Discipleship Director:  <br />
  Student and Small Group Ministries</h3>
<p>First Presbyterian Church of Fairfield is calling for a faithful, imaginative and discerning lifelong learner in the Reformed tradition, with a reflective reverence for the authority of scripture, who meets and encourages people where they are in their faith journey.  We seek a genuine, collaborative and non-hierarchical Christian leader to shepherd our student ministries and our small group ministries so that participants may find and then demonstrate a deeper commitment of faith in God and fellowship with one another through Jesus Christ.  This position is a non-ordained position.</p>
<h3>Position Overview:</h3>
<p>In line with the overall mission of the First Presbyterian Church of Fairfield, and under the general direction of the Pastor with support from the Christian Education and Discipleship (CE&amp;D) Committee, the Discipleship Director will attract, build and sustain a robust volunteer community for each church ministry so that our ministries may flourish within our congregation. The Discipleship Director will grow, strengthen and oversee all aspects of our student ministry, provide guidance and administrative support to our small group ministry, and provide spiritual support and guidance to our children&rsquo;s ministry. </p>
<h3>Job Responsibilities:</h3>
<p><strong><em>Attract, build, and sustain a robust volunteer community</em></strong> within the church for each church ministry so that the congregation will be able to better use their God-given talent, time and resources to grow and strengthen all of our church ministries. </p>
<p><strong><em>Grow a more vibrant Student Ministry</em></strong>, mentoring and spiritually empowering students, parents and dedicated volunteers by exemplifying and championing our Student Ministry Mission and Values.</p>
<p><strong><em>Provide spiritual support, coordination and administrative oversight to our small group ministry</em></strong> meeting regularly with small group leaders and working in conjunction with the Pastor to design and support the content of the programs.</p>
<p><strong><em>Provide spiritual support and guidance to the Children&rsquo;s Ministry</em></strong> meeting regularly with the CE&amp;D chair and Children&rsquo;s Ministry committee and proactively providing advice, spiritual guidance and support to the ministry as needed.</p>
<h3>Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Minimum 4 year college degree in ministry from an accredited school.</li>
  <li>Some xperience in student ministry or Christian education preferred. </li>
  <li>Versed in and compatible with Reformed teaching and doctrine.</li>
  <li>Strong interpersonal and organizational skills.  </li>
  <li>Ability to communicate effectively with students, parents and the congregation through various communication vehicles (verbal, written, postings, newsletters, email, texting etc.)</li>
</ul>
